In this episode of Major Issues, the hosts dive into Marvel Studios’ latest animated series, Marvel Zombies (2025). They explore how the show expands on the What If…? universe, the brutal tone it embraces, and the surprising character arcs of heroes like Kamala Khan, Blade, Red Guardian, and Shang-Chi. The crew compares the series to its comic book roots, debates whether its four-episode run helps or hurts the story, and looks ahead at what this blood-soaked experiment means for Marvel’s future in animation. Spoilers ahead—this one gets messy

